<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-04-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="490" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d490">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Riddle</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                            Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-04"><hi rend="italic">April 4,
                                        1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>(Mr. Riddle states that the Russian Government is sending
                                instructions by telegraph to Russian ambassador to Turkey that if
                                Turkish Government ratifies the convention it should at the same
                                time assent to Russian circular regarding nonsignatories.)</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>